						<summary>

						<p>Inscribed fragment (No. 2) from a field near the palace area of excavation site No. 7.</p>						

						<p>Undated. Palaeographically datable to the Brāhmī of 3rd century A.D. Written in the Prākṛit language.</p>						

						<p>Seems to refer to the gift of a pillar. Mentions a <hi rend="italic">Kulaputra.</hi></p>						

